*****
[1] New York (western counties)
Date: Wed 11 Nov 2015
Source: WHEC [edited]
http://www.whec.com/article/stories/s3960499.shtml


7 cases of whooping cough have been reported in the Batavia school district so far in 2015. In Rochester, there has been a reported case of an elementary student with whooping cough. There have also been reported cases in Geneseo.

The Monroe county health department is asking parents be mindful that there was 1 case in a city. If your child develops a persisting cough and it's not getting better, they need to see a doctor.

Parents of children at the school on Webster Avenue in the city were sent a letter about the whooping cough cases. It reads in part, "We are writing to inform you that the county health department has confirmed a case of pertussis, also known as whooping cough, in a student at our school."

In Monroe County, we're told they're seeing more pertussis cases. County health representatives say there are between 50-100 cases a year now compared to 10 years ago, when there were only about 10-20 cases a year.

[Byline: Rebecca Fath]

