*****
[3] Virginia (Albemarle County)
Date: Thu 12 Nov 2015
Source: NBC29 [edited]
http://www.nbc29.com/story/30502641/case-of-whooping-cough-at-wahs


Western Albemarle High School has a confirmed case of whooping cough. Schools sent a note to parents Thursday, 12 Nov 2015, to inform them of the situation. Whooping cough, or pertussis, is spread through the air by coughing.

The note says casual contact in a classroom setting usually does not warrant routine preventative treatment. However, it does urge parents to take their children to a doctor if they cough for more than 2 weeks or it happens in fits and spasms.

